				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13424508#post-4706235</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13424508/scp-4752#post-4706235</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 01 Jul 2020 16:49:26 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Buttfranklin</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2721810</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>This is a single metaphor delivered in a jejune, slapdash manner. I didn't really understand what the mountain was supposed to look like from the initial description (how is the &quot;triangle&quot; oriented? is the &quot;triangle&quot; visible from a bird's eye view or from the ground? is this &quot;curved&quot; hypotenuse concave or convex?) until I backfilled it at the end. For this metaphor to work, the whole silhouette of the mountain has to change shape but it isn't clear if this happens.</p> <p>It's also thematically unsatisfying for me that this piece is so short and devoid of tension when the anomaly and the economic crash are so gigantic.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
